	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64135803">The thing is, these plasticisers aren't chemically bonded to the plastics they're mixed with, and it doesn't take much, e.g. heat, salt, fats, &amp;/or acid (basically the properties of most foods), to leech them out of the plastic &amp; into the food. I've tried avoiding plastics, e.g. buying liquids in glass containers, not using plastic containers for food storage, buying produce by the kilo so that it's not pre-packaged in plastic, etc.. It's not easy &amp; impossible to exclude most of your food from h</div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64135803">

</div>
